issue.body:
@droark 

These are some changes to depends to try to get the OS X Gitian descriptor working. I realized I never committed the OS X descriptor, so this branch was originally intented to commit the OS X descriptor. Currently it does not include the OS X descriptor, because I haven't been able to fully test it due to the depends system using Python 3, but the Armory code still using Python 2. That causes a conflict when building _CppBlockUtils.so. However, the Gitian build does get as far as building _CppBlockUtils.so, so I can just commit the descriptor now if you want.

I also included a commit from theuni that I got from the Bitcoin Core repo. I was doing it to try to resolve an issue I was having (turned out to not fix the issue, something else did), but I'll leave it, because I figure it is good to try to keep up with relevant changes to the depends system in Bitcoin Core.
